  <!-- FIX GUIDE -->
  <div class="section-head fade-up d5" style="margin-top:64px">
    <h2>Deployment Fix Guide</h2>
    <div class="sh-line"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="fix-guide fade-up d6">
    <div class="fix-guide-header">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 000 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 001.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 01-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 01-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 017.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/></svg>
      <div class="fix-guide-title">Three Steps to Fix the Failing Workflow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fix-steps">
      <div class="fix-step">
        <div class="fix-step-num">01</div>
        <div class="fix-step-title">Enable GitHub Pages</div>
        <div class="fix-step-desc">Go to your repository → <strong style="color:var(--text-light)">Settings</strong> → <strong style="color:var(--text-light)">Pages</strong>. Under <em>Source</em>, select <strong style="color:var(--gold)">"GitHub Actions"</strong>. This tells GitHub to accept deployments from your workflow file.</div>
        <div class="code-inline">Settings → Pages → Source:<br/>GitHub Actions ✓</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fix-step">
        <div class="fix-step-num">02</div>
        <div class="fix-step-title">Fix Permissions</div>
        <div class="fix-step-desc">Your <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">static.yml</code> must include the correct permissions block. Without <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">pages: write</code> and <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">id-token: write</code>, the deploy step will always fail.</div>
        <div class="code-inline">permissions:<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;pages: write<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;id-token: write<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;contents: read</div>
      </div>
      <div class="fix-step">
        <div class="fix-step-num">03</div>
        <div class="fix-step-title">Replace Your YAML</div>
        <div class="fix-step-desc">Copy the recommended <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">static.yml</code> shown above into your <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">.github/workflows/</code> folder, commit it to <code style="font-family:'Courier Prime',monospace;color:var(--gold)">main</code>, and the next run should succeed.</div>
        <div class="code-inline">git add .github/workflows/static.yml<br/>git commit -m "fix: pages deploy"<br/>git push origin main</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

